-- 
Zimbabwe Licenses Chinese, UAE Diamond Miners, Standard Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-03-14T10:43:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/zimbabwe-licenses-chinese-uae-diamond-miners-standard-reports.html
Zimbabwe Mining Development Corp.
will mine diamonds with  China ’s Sino Zimbabwe and Pure Dian of
the  United Arab Emirates  in the Marange diamond fields, the
 Standard  reported, citing ZMDC Chairman Godwills Masimirembwa.  The state-owned mining company is already working with
China’s Anjin Mining, Mbada Mining Ltd. and Canadile Miners Ltd.
at Marange, the Harare-based newspaper cited Masimirembwa as
saying. ZMDC received about 150 applications to dig for diamonds
at the field, the Standard reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in London at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  